23/10/2002
BRATISLAVA, Slovakia -- Yugoslav Army Chief of Staff Branko Krga met Tuesday (22 October) with his Slovak counterpart and said that Yugoslavia expects to join the Partnership for Peace programme at NATO's summit in Prague next month. 
Gen Krga and Slovakia's Milan Cerovski discussed military reforms as well as Bratislava's experience in meeting NATO accession criteria.
Also on Tuesday, an EU delegation wrapped up a visit to Belgrade.The delegation delivered a message from EU foreign affairs chief Javier Solana urging state and federal authorities to adopt the new constitutional charter by 7 November. 
(B92, Tanjug - 22/10/02)
